properties.name: RecoveryPointObjectiveRPO
properties.description: The Recovery Point Objective (RPO) determines the maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time.Four levels of RPO need to be specified:- Critical (maximum tolerable data loss is seconds)- Serious (maximum tolerable data loss is minutes)- Significant (maximum tolerable data loss is hours)- Minor (maximum tolerable data loss is days)

properties.name: RecoveryTimeObjectiveRTO
properties.description: The Recovery Time Objective (RTO) determines the maximum tolerable amount of time needed to bring all critical systems back online. This covers, for example, restore data from back-up or fix of a failure.Four levels of RTO need to be specified:- Critical (maximum tolerable amount of time needed to bring all critical systems back online is seconds)- Serious (maximum tolerable amount of time needed to bring all critical systems back online is minutes)- Significant (maximum tolerable amount of time needed to bring all critical systems back online is hours)- Minor (maximum tolerable amount of time needed to bring all critical systems back online is days)

properties.name: WorkRecoveryTimeWRT
properties.description: The Work Recovery Time (WRT) determines the maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity. This could be, for example, checking the databases and logs, making sure the applications or services are running and are available.Four levels of WRT need to be specified:- Critical (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is seconds)- Serious (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is minutes)- Significant (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is hours)- Minor (maximum tolerable amount of time that is needed to verify the system and or data integrity is days)

properties.name: MaximumTolerableDowntimeMTD
properties.description: Maximum Tolerable Downtime (MTD) determines the maximum time a business can tolerate the absence or unavailability of a particular application.Downtime consists of two elements, the Recovery Time Objective and the Work Recovery Time: MTD = RTO + WRTMTD level will be calculated automatically according to RTO and WRT levels, it cannot be modified manually.-	Critical (maximum tolerable downtime is seconds)-	Serious (maximum tolerable downtime is minutes)-	Significant (maximum tolerable downtime is hours)-	Minor (maximum tolerable downtime is days)

properties.name: SLALevel
